## Variance Decomposition (Memorized)
1. Volume = (Actual vol âˆ’ Budget vol) Ã— Budget CPP
2. Site Mix = Actual vol Ã— (Weighted budget CPP at actual mix âˆ’ Overall budget CPP)
3. Rate = Actual vol Ã— (Actual CPP âˆ’ Weighted budget CPP at actual mix)
   Break into: Stop Fee, B2C, Weight, Ad Hoc, RBS, Pickup
4. Unexplained = Total âˆ’ sum (must be < 2%)

Bridge order (Lâ†’R): Budget â†’ Volume â†’ B2C â†’ Stop Fee â†’ Weight â†’ Ad Hoc â†’ RBS â†’ Pickup â†’ Actual

## Red Flags (Always Check)
- CPPâ†‘ while volume flat/up = rate problem
- Single facility >40% of total variance = concentration risk
- Ad hoc >10% of total variance = investigate
- CPPâ†‘ AND volumeâ†“ at same facility = double whammy, ALWAYS flag

